rical significance, along with suggestions for further reading and research.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aChinese literaturey220-589xHistory and criticism. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh1 aAshmore, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenn, James A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerkowitz, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBokenkamp, Stephen R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampany, Robert Ford, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampany, Robert Ford, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aChapman, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChen, Huaiyu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChen, Jack W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChoo, Jessey J. C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChoo, Jessey, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDavis, Timothy M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDien, Albert E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarmer, J. Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolcombe, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHudson, Clarke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnapp, Keith N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnechtges, David R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKroll, Paul W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLee, Jen-Der, econtributor.4